Why Security Matters?
A single misconfiguration can expose the entire infrastructure.

Disable Root Login:
Edit:
sudo vi /etc/ssh/sshd_config

Change:
PermitRootLogin no

Restart SSH:
sudo systemctl restart sshd

Use SSH Keys:
Generate Key:
ssh-keygen

Copy Key:
ssh-copy-id user@server
Configure Firewall

Ubuntu:
sudo ufw enable

Allow SSH:
sudo ufw allow 22

Check Status:
sudo ufw status
Update Packages
sudo apt update
sudo apt upgrade 

Real-Time DevOps Scenario:
Secure Jenkins Server
sudo ufw allow 8080
sudo ufw allow 22
sudo ufw deny 80
